<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565450>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 11. Matsucoccus krystalae Ahmed and Miller, n.sp. Adult female. Broward Co., Proglis Warehouse, Pompano Beach, Florida, March 23, 2018, on Pinus ellottii, J. Farnum. A) Antenna. B) Thoracic spiracle. C) Long filamentous setae. D) Hind tibia, tarsus, claw. E) Short filamentous seta. F) Multilocular pore. G) Seventh abdominal spiracle. H) Abdomen bent under body shifting abdominal apex under segments IV, V, or VI. I) Dorsal filamentous seta. J) Bilocular tubular ducts. K) Cicatrices." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4565450/files/figure.png" .

